      "writtenOn": "2020-12-15T19:22:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry for being unclear.  On the task scheduler, we sync the main repo and all of its dependencies into a temporary directory, eg. /tmp/123.  We have some repos (eg. lottie-ci) which sync Skia as a sibling, so we\u0027d end up with /tmp/123/skia and /tmp/123/lottie-ci.  That repo may have CasSpecs which point to files in both lottie-ci and skia, eg. \u0027../skia/tools/some-tool.sh\u0027, \u0027../lottie-ci/tools/another-tool.sh\u0027.  If we just assume that the first path component can be removed, validation will fail in cases like this.",
      "parentUuid": "efaf510f_55a75dc1",
